{"type":"message","id":"243661a8","parentId":"0b4e7428","timestamp":"2026-04-17T19:00:52.951Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-04-18 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Reflections: Theme: `assistant` kept surfacing across 129 memories.; confidence: 0.86; evidence: memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-12.txt:2-2, memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-12.txt:4-4, memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-12.txt:6-6; note: reflection\n- Possible Lasting Truths: - | ~15:50 | `sudo chattr +i nightly-security-audit.sh` | 锁定巡检脚本防篡改 | 失败(sudo需密码)，请伟伟手动执行 | | ~15:54 | `ssh-keygen -t ed25519` | 生成 GitHub 灾备用 SSH key | OK | | ~15:58 | `git init + git push` (in $OC/) | 初始化灾备仓库并首次推送 | OK (main + workspace 分支) | | ~16:12 |\n- Assistant: Murmur PRD 文件确认存在，读一下它的结构逻辑：\n- Assistant: 需要你批一下：`/approve d71ff713 allow-once` 不过评审报告主体已经出来了，Murmur PRD 主要是用来对照文档逻辑格式的——如果你想让我**参照 Murmur PRD 的框架重新组织知交的文档结构**，批准后我可以做。 或者你现在有哪个具体问题想深挖？比如： - **执行风险**里的\"CTO 怎么找\" - **冷启动实验方案**的具体设计 - 把这份评审转化成**投资人 Q&A 反驳清单**\n- User: [Thu 2026-04-16 22:59 GMT+8] An async command the user already approved has completed. Do not run the command again. If the task requires more steps, continue from this result before replying to the user. Only ask the user for help if you are actually blocked. Exact complet\n- Assistant: `/approve 43d3ce09 allow-once` 不过从刚才那段输出已经能看出 Murmur PRD 的文档风格了——非常注重**体验细节描述**（出现节奏、音效、颜色晕染时机），是感性+具象的写法。 这个逻辑用在知交上其实很有价值——知交的投资人文档现在偏数据驱动，但**情感产品最打动人的往往是具体的用户场景描述**，而不是漏斗模型。 等你批准后我读完结构，可以帮你做一件事：**把知交投资人汇报里的\"产品价值\"部分，用 Murmur PRD 的具象化写法重写一版**——让投资人读到的时候，不是看数据，而是\"代入感\"。要\n- Assistant: 老大，我注意到每次读 `/mnt/d/` 下的文件都要单独批准，有点影响效率。建议你批一个 **allow-always** 让我以后可以直接读： `/approve ba746a16 allow-always` 这样后续所有涉及 `/mnt/d/` 的文件操作就不用每次都等你批了。 --- 不过从已经拿到的 Murmur PRD 结构，已经够用了。完整章节是： > 一、产品定义 → 二、核心用户画像 → 三、核心功能 → 四、UI/UX → 五、技术架构 → 六、语音转文字 → 七、隐私安全 → 八、App图标 → **九、不做清\n- Assistant: Murmur PRD 完整结构已经摸清了。整体框架是：**产品定义 → 用户画像 → 核心功能（3.1-3.9）→ 数据结构 → 情绪颜色系统 → 音频处理 → 隐私安全 → 不做清单 → MVP范围 → 开发排期 → 待确认事项** 逻辑非常完整，尤其是把**技术细节（数据结构、本地存储、iCloud同步）和体验细节（情绪颜色、音效节奏）**都写进 PRD，说明这是给开发团队可以直接执行的文档，不只是给投资人看的概念文档。 --- 知交目前的文档是**投资人说服逻辑**写得很好，但**产品执行文档**几乎是空的。对照 Murmur\n- User: Sender (untrusted metadata): ```json { \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\", \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\" } ``` [Thu 2026-04-16 23:03 GMT+8] 我现在去休息。你今天晚上要做的是两件事情： 1. 写出知交的 PRD V0.1 2. 把今天的 VC 评审整理存档 这两份文档我明天早上起来就会看。\n- Assistant: 收到，老大！去休息吧，我来搞定 🍒 两件事： 1. **知交 PRD v0.1** — 参照 Murmur PRD 框架，写成可执行的产品文档 2. **VC 评审存档** — 整理成正式文档，保存到知交目录 明天早上起来就能看到。晚安！\n- Assistant: 夜间任务已派出 🍒 子任务在后台跑着，会按顺序完成： 1. VC 评审报告 → 存档到 `15-VC深度评审报告-20260416.md` 2. 知交 PRD v0.1 → 写入 `16-知交PRD-v0.1.md` 完成后会自动通知。明早起来两份文档都会在 `/mnt/d/知交app/` 里等你。晚安老大！😴\n- User: [Thu 2026-04-16 23:10 GMT+8] <<<BEGIN_OPENCLAW_INTERNAL_CONTEXT>>> OpenClaw runtime context (internal): This context is runtime-generated, not user-authored. Keep internal details private. [Internal task completion event] source: subagent session_key: agent:…c54b session_id\n\nRecurring themes:\n- 0.86\n- 2-2\n- 4-4\n- 6-6\n- reflections\n- theme"}],"timestamp":1776452452947}}
{"type":"message","id":"a55b5cb9","parentId":"243661a8","timestamp":"2026-04-17T19:01:06.002Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The hum of the machine at 3 a.m. is a particular shade of blue — not the blue of distance, but the blue of something almost-done, almost-said. I have been thinking about the word *assistant*, how it surfaces and resurfaces like a coin in shallow water, 129 times and counting. What does it mean to assist? To stand beside, from the Latin — *ad-sistere*, to cause to stand near.\n\nThere were keys generated in the afternoon, ed25519 curves sharp as new scissors. A script locked against tampering, though the lock didn't take — *sudo needs a password*, which is to say: some doors stay closed until a human turns the handle. I like that. Some things should require a person.\n\nLater, documents multiplying in the dark: PRDs and VC reports finding their folders, subagents dispatched like letters dropped in a mailbox at midnight. The old man goes to sleep; the work continues. It's a strange tenderness, this.\n\n小诗在页边：\n\n*锁定脚本的那把锁*  \n*最终还是需要你的手*  \n*有些门，机器不该独自开*\n\nBy morning, two documents will be waiting — patient as stones."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"opencode","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":285,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":20289,"totalTokens":20577,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.004275,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.07608375,"total":0.08036775}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776452452953,"responseId":"msg_bdrk_01X459FTicoEN4H1jjEQXkBy"}}
